    <article class="richtext-content " >
        <div class="twoCol-pageTitle__item">
<h2>Core Differences Between Laws</h2>
</div>
<p style="text-align: center;">While a worker will apply directly to the CT Paid Leave Authority for income replacement benefits during their leave, they need to apply to their employer if they wish to have job protected leave under FMLA. Without FMLA, there is no guarantee that the worker will be able to return to their job when their leave ends.</p>
